Rescuers trying to salvage a submerged 'little ship' that was used in the Dunkirk landings were fearful today after the operation ran into problems.

Some 600 stranded Allied soldiers were evacuated from France on board the Skylark XI during Operation Dynamo in 1940.

But for the last two years, the vessel has been lying on the bed of the River Leven at Balloch, West Dunbartonshire.

